                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Petersburg</placeName>\n                <date>June 12th 1854</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                <placeName>Phila.</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dr Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Enclosed I hand you<lb/> draft on <persName>Driscel<add>?</add>\n                    &amp; Co</persName> your city for 151 47/100 Dolls<lb/> being the amount paid in\n                for your works<lb/> sent me, and subscriptions to Occident—as pr<lb/> statement\n                annexed—I have the remainder of<lb/> the books here—subject to your order—I do<lb/>\n                not think the prospect of selling them here<lb/> is very good—however I will use my\n                best<lb/> endeavours for your interest. <persName>Sol Myers</persName> has<lb/>\n                removed to <placeName>Richmond</placeName> &amp; I will send him his<lb/> Bible by\n                first opportunity &amp; collect the amt.<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Feldenheimer</persName> has removed to <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>.<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Kating</persName> says he only took your Occident for<lb/> about four\n                mos. and consequently did not pay<lb/> me. <persName>Mr B. A. Davis</persName>\n                declined purchasing the set<lb/> Prayer Books. Doubtlessly you have thought me<lb/>\n                very remiss in not attending to this matter before<lb/>\n                <del>this</del>—and not without reason, for a long time<lb/> has elapsed since the\n                receipt of your letter—but<lb/> really the cares and duties of business have\n                been<lb/> so very pressing as to leave me little leisure<lb/> to attend to any\n                business entrusted to me</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p34b2xr1z/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
